Gauteng MEC for education, Panyaza Lesufi is holding a consultative meeting to map a way forward. Editor's note: Livestream courtesy DStv 403, you can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng MEC for education, Panyaza Lesufi, is holding a consultative meeting to map a way forward. Several South African schools have turned into crime scenes this year. READ: Basic Education Department slams call to arm teachers Most recently, Forest High pupil Daniel Bakwela was stabbed to death. And, in Durban, teacher S’boniso Nyawose was murdered by an intruder at Masuku Primary School. The Educators' Union of South Africa wants the government to allow teachers to arm themselves when reporting for duty. The union said the government has constantly failed to secure educators in schools. The Department of Basic Education has slammed the call. It said the union is not registered.